title: iOS build is broken
body:
An excerpt:

``` bash
warning: dropping unsupported crate type `dylib` for target `armv7-apple-ios`
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/lib.rs:116:12: 116:26 warning: feature is deprecated and will only be available for a limited time, please rewrite code that relies on it
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/lib.rs:116 #![feature(old_impl_check)]
                                                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/lib.rs:116:12: 116:26 warning: feature is deprecated and will only be available for a limited time, please rewrite code that relies on it
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/lib.rs:116 #![feature(old_impl_check)]
                                                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/env.rs:569:42: 569:63 error: unresolved name `super::os::DLL_PREFIX`
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/env.rs:569     pub const DLL_PREFIX: &'static str = super::os::DLL_PREFIX;
                                                                                     ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/env.rs:574:42: 574:63 error: unresolved name `super::os::DLL_SUFFIX`
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/env.rs:574     pub const DLL_SUFFIX: &'static str = super::os::DLL_SUFFIX;
                                                                                     ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/env.rs:579:45: 579:69 error: unresolved name `super::os::DLL_EXTENSION`
/Users/drew/Code/rust/src/libstd/env.rs:579     pub const DLL_EXTENSION: &'static str = super::os::DLL_EXTENSION;
                                                                                        ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
error: aborting due to 3 previous errors
make: *** [x86_64-apple-darwin/stage2/lib/rustlib/armv7-apple-ios/lib/stamp.std] Error 101
```

configured with

`../configure --target=armv7-apple-ios,armv7s-apple-ios,i386-apple-ios,aarch64-apple-ios,x86_64-apple-ios && make`

This has been going on for a few days to a week, but I have only recently isolated it to the iOS cross-compile.
